title: Bisikan
description:
Bisikan is a mini-album by Noh Salleh, released on April 18, 2020 through his own label, Hujan Selaseh Sdn Bhd/Noh Phrofile Enterprise. It is a follow-up to his debut studio album, Angin Kencang (2018).

The album consists of four songs, all of which were written and produced by Noh Salleh. The songs on the album explore themes of love, loss, and hope.

The title track, "Bisikan", is a song about a whisper that is heard in the middle of the night. The song is about the power of words and the importance of listening to our intuition.

The other songs on the album are "Cinta Tak Lama", "Mau Ke Mana", and "Debu".

Bisikan was a commercial success, reaching number one on the Malaysian iTunes chart. The album was also well-received by critics, who praised Noh Salleh's songwriting and production

title: Angin Kencang
description:
Angin Kencang is the debut studio album by Malaysian singer and songwriter Noh Salleh. It was released on February 20, 2018 by the record labels Hujan Selaseh Sdn Bhd and Demajors. The album consists of 10 songs, all of which were written and produced by Noh Salleh.

The songs in the album explore themes of love, loss, and hope. The music in the album is dominated by the pop folk and acoustic genres, with poetic lyrics that tell the story of Noh Salleh's life, full of ups and downs.

Angin Kencang was well-received by critics and fans. The album was nominated for the Best Album at the 2019 Anugerah Industri Muzik Malaysia (AIM)

title: Berhati
description:
Berhati is the debut studio album by Indonesian singer-songwriter Sal Priadi. It was released on February 20, 2020 through the record labels Orang Pertunjukkan and Kijn.

The album Berhati was produced by Kara Putri Mindyani and Sal Priadi himself. The music in this album is dominated by the pop folk and acoustic genres, with poetic lyrics that tell stories about love, loss, and hope.

The album Berhati received positive reception from critics and fans. The album was nominated for the Best Album at the 2021 Anugerah Musik Indonesia

title: Selamat Ulang Tahun
description:
Selamat Ulang Tahun (Happy Birthday) is a song by Nadin Amizah, released on May 28, 2020 through the record label Sorai. It is the first single from her debut studio album, Selamat Ulang Tahun.The song was written by Nadin Amizah and produced by Laleilmanino. It is a pop song with poetic lyrics that tell the story of Nadin Amizah's life, full of ups and downs.

The song Selamat Ulang Tahun received positive reception from critics and fans. It was nominated for the Best Song at the 2021 Anugerah Musik Indonesia.

title: Kalah Bertaruh
description:
Kalah Bertaruh is a mini-album by Nadin Amizah, released on May 26, 2021 through the record label Sorai. It is a follow-up to her debut studio album, Selamat Ulang Tahun.

The album consists of five songs, all of which were written and produced by Nadin Amizah and Laleilmanino. The songs on the album explore themes of love, loss, and hope.

The title track, "Kalah Bertaruh", is a song about a relationship that has come to an end. The song is about the pain of loss and the hope of finding love again.

The other songs on the album are "Sebuah Tarian yang Tak Kunjung Selesai", "Hormat kepada Angin", "Seperti Takdir Kita yang Tulis", and "Menangis di Jalan Pulang".

Kalah Bertaruh was a commercial success, reaching number one on the Indonesian iTunes chart. The album was also well-received by critics, who praised Nadin Amizah's songwriting and Laleilmanino's production.

title: Dunia Batas
description: Dunia Batas adalah sebuah album studio kedua karya Payung Teduh yang dirilis pada 1 April 2012[1] dengan label Ivy League Music yang merupakan sebuah label indie. Album ini dirilis dalam format CD yang kemudian pada 11 November 2014, pihak label mengumumkan link digital download.[2] Pada Record Store Day Indonesia (18-19 April 2015), album ini dirilis dalam bentuk kaset secara terbatas sebanyak 300 keping.

title: Live at Yamaha Live and Loud
description: Live at Yamaha Live and Loud is a live album by Indonesian indie pop band Payung Teduh. It was released in 2016 by Payung Teduh and produced by Payung Teduh and Danang Pamungkas.The album was recorded live at the Yamaha Live and Loud concert in Jakarta on December 10, 2015. The concert was part of the Yamaha Live and Loud series, which featured a number of Indonesian indie bands.

title: Ruang Tunggu
description:
Ruang Tunggu is the fourth studio album by Indonesian indie folk band Payung Teduh. It was released on December 19, 2017 by Parara Records.Ruang Tunggu is a very different album from Payung Teduh's previous albums. This album focuses more on folk and acoustic music, with more poetic and philosophical lyrics. This album was also recorded with a simpler musical arrangement, with only a few instruments used.Although different from previous albums, Ruang Tunggu is still a very good album. This album successfully maintains Payung Teduh's trademark, which is beautiful and calming music, with poetic and inspiring lyrics.

This album also became one of the best-selling albums in Indonesia in 2017. Songs from this album, such as "Akad", "Di Atas Meja", and "Sisa Kebahagiaan", became very popular and were sung by many Indonesian people.

title: Mendengar Suara
description:
Mendengar Suara 2018 is a mini-album by the Indonesian folk music group Payung Teduh. It was released on August 2, 2018 by the record label Parara Records.

This is Payung Teduh's first mini-album since their studio album titled Ruang Tunggu in 2017. The album contains 10 songs, including the song "Mendengar Suara" which is the main song of the album.

The lyrics of the songs in this album tell stories about various things, such as love, loss, and hope. The music in this album is dominated by acoustic instruments, such as guitar, violin, and piano.

The Mendengar Suara 2018 album received positive reception from critics and fans. The album was nominated for the Best Album at the 2019 Anugerah Musik Indonesia.

title: Certified Lover Boy
description: Certified Lover Boy is the sixth studio album by Canadian rapper and singer Drake, released on September 3, 2021, by OVO Sound and Republic Records. Its production was handled by frequent collaborators 40, Nineteen85, PartyNextDoor, OZ, and Vinylz, among others.

title: Her Loss
description: Her Loss is a collaborative studio album by Canadian rapper Drake and Atlanta-based rapper 21 Savage. It was released on November 4, 2022, through OVO Sound and Republic Records. The album features a sole guest appearance from Travis Scott.

title: Lelaku
description:
Lelaku is the debut studio album by Indonesian indie folk band Fourtwnty. It was released on May 25, 2016 through Demajors. 
Lelaku album cover by FourtwntyOpens in a new window. The album consists of 10 songs, all of which were written and produced by Fourtwnty. The songs on the album explore themes of love, loss, and personal growth.

The title track, "Lelaku", is a song about a journey of self-discovery. The song is about the importance of following your heart and living your own truth.

The other songs on the album are "Aku Tenang", "Diam-Diam Ku Bawa", "Hitam Putih", "Argumentasi Dimensi", "Iritasi Ringan", "Fana Merah Jambu", "Puisi Alam", "Aku Bukan Binatang", and "Diskusi Senja".

Lelaku was a commercial success, reaching number one on the Indonesian iTunes chart. The album was also well-received by critics, who praised Fourtwnty's songwriting and production.

title: Ego & Fungsi Otak
description:
Ego & Fungsi Otak is the third studio album by Indonesian indie folk band Fourtwnty. It was released on August 17, 2018 through Demajors. Ego & Fungsi Otak album cover by Fourtwnty

The album consists of 7 songs, all of which were written and produced by Fourtwnty. The songs on the album explore themes of love, loss, and personal growth.

The title track, "Ego & Fungsi Otak", is a song about the importance of balance between the ego and the mind. The song is about the need to be aware of our ego and to use our mind to control it.

The other songs on the album are "Sisa Kebahagiaan", "Kusut", "Mendengar Suara", "Lagu Duka", "Tertawalah", and "Trilogi".

Ego & Fungsi Otak was a commercial success, reaching number one on the Indonesian iTunes chart. The album was also well-received by critics, who praised Fourtwnty's songwriting and production.

title: Nalar
description:
Nalar is the fourth studio album by Indonesian indie folk band Fourtwnty. It was released on April 18, 2023 through Demajors. 
The album consists of 10 songs, all of which were written and produced by Fourtwnty. The songs on the album explore themes of love, loss, and mental health.

The title track, "Nalar", is a song about the importance of using logic and reason to navigate through life. The song is about the need to be aware of our emotions and to use logic to make decisions.

The other songs on the album are "Aku Mencintai Traumaku", "Larasuka", "Aku = Kamu", "Besi Tua", "High", "Rammang-Rammang", "Mangu", "Pintu Keluar", and "Menangisi Traumaku".

Nalar was a commercial success, reaching number one on the Indonesian iTunes chart. The album was also well-received by critics, who praised Fourtwnty's songwriting and production.

title: Heroes & Villains
description: Heroes & Villains is the second studio album by American record producer Metro Boomin. It was released through Republic Records and Boominati on December 2, 2022. The album contains guest appearances from John Legend, Future, Chris Brown, Don Toliver, Travis Scott, 21 Savage, Young Nudy, Young Thug, the Weeknd, Mustafa, ASAP Rocky, the late Takeoff, and Gunna. Production was mainly handled by Metro himself, alongside TM88, DJ Moon, Peter Lee Johnson, Johan Lenox, Allen Ritter, David x Eli, Honorable C.N.O.T.E., Scriptplugg, Prince85, Oz, Nik D, D. Rich, DaHeala, My Best Friend Jacob, Elkan, Simon on the Moon, and Xz. A psychedelic trap album, ASAP Rocky and Morgan Freeman serve as its narrators.[1] The album serves as the sequel to Metro's previous album, Not All Heroes Wear Capes (2018), and serves as the second project for a trilogy. A instrumental version of the album, titled the "Heroes Version", was released on December 5, 2022. A chopped not slopped remix edition of the album by OG Ron C and DJ Candlestick, titled the "Villains Version", was released on February 17, 2023. Heroes & Villains debuted at the top of the US Billboard 200, with 185,000 album-equivalent units sold in its first week of release, making it Metro's third number one album.

title: Not All Heroes Wear Capes
description: Not All Heroes Wear Capes (stylized in all caps) is the debut studio album by American record producer Metro Boomin. It was released by Boominati Worldwide and Republic Records on November 2, 2018. The album features guest appearances from Gucci Mane, Travis Scott, 21 Savage, Swae Lee, Gunna, Young Thug, Wizkid, J. Balvin, Offset, Kodak Black, and Drake.[1] The deluxe edition of the album was released, consisting of the instrumental versions of all songs from the standard edition on November 6, 2018. The album is the first part of a trilogy, with the second part being its sequel, Metro's second studio album, Heroes & Villains, which was released on December 2, 2022.

title: Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse
description: Metro Boomin created the original soundtrack for Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse. It was released through Boominati Worldwide and Republic Records on June 2, 2023. It contains guest appearances from Swae Lee, Lil Wayne, Offset, ASAP Rocky, Roisee, Future, Lil Uzi Vert, JID, James Blake, Nav, A Boogie wit da Hoodie, Ei8ht, Don Toliver, Wizkid, Beam, Toian, Coi Leray, 21 Savage, 2 Chainz, and Nas. The deluxe version of the soundtrack was released three days later, on June 5, 2023. It contains additional songs performed by other artists, consisting of Mora, Becky G, Ayra Starr, Shenseea, Myke Towers, Big Boss Vette, Omah Lay, and Pop Money
